### [sub](https://docs.dolphindb.com/en/Functions/s/sub.html)



#### Syntax

sub(X, Y) or X-Y

#### Arguments

**X**/**Y** is a scalar/pair/vector/matrix/set. If one of *X* and *Y* is a pair/vector/matrix, the other is a scalar or a pair/vector/matrix of the same size.

#### Details

Return the result of element-by-element subtracting *Y* from *X*. If both *X* and *Y* are sets, sub returns a set by eliminating the common elements of *X* and *Y* from *X*.

#### Examples

```
